div.p:
1. Continued availability to the West of the Congoʼs key primary products, on
                    terms both advantageous to the Congo and commensurate with the requirements of
                    world market stability;

2. Ready access to the growing Congolese industrial and consumer markets for
                    American exporters, on at least an equal basis with suppliers from other
                    countries;

5. Continued availability and easy access to Congolese airfields for US aircraft,
                    particularly those engaged in surveillance of South Atlantic waters and those
                    transiting Africa toward Indian Ocean destinations;
